commit.message:
Fix long-standing issues with copying/operating on DisorderedAtoms. (#3223)

* Call generate_full_id instead of reset_full_id if full_id is None.

* Add copy method to DisorderedEntityWrapper to allow recursive copying of SMCRA objects

* Catch situations when Atom parent is empty: eg copying disordered atoms

* Actually assign full id after generating

* Add an explicit transform method to DisorderedAtom that propagates transforms to children

* Add tests for disordered entities/atoms.

* Trigger

run doc8 via pre-commit

Remove some pre-commit exclusions

Given these are restricted to python (and shell scripts)
there is no need to exclude the tests folder.

The rst-lint aka restructuredtext-lint author
did not want to support the pre-commit system.

Using rstcheck as an alternative which also
wraps docutils internally.
Include rstcheck in pre-commit

Makes for clearer logging of setup time vs linting time.

commit.message:
TravisCI: Use pre-commit for flake8 etc

Still have some style checks via Tox which have not yet
been implemented in the pre-commit hook.

Also, deliberately still running black separately from
pre-commit in order to balance the run time of the two
TravisCI jobs in the the basics stage.
Manually fix comment placement after black

These are not black dependencies

Rather doc8 and rst-lint are additional tools we
would like to include in pre-commit in their own
right.
Blacken docs (testing pre-commit hook)

Remove pre-commit trailing-whitespace on Python files.

This breaks multiple doctests.

Need black --check with --diff

Otherwise it shows any diff, but without a error value.
black
Not enforcing flake8-commas, flake8-pie, or flake8-sfs
